                            <tr>
                                <td align="left" valign="top" class="Newsletter border_top_left border_bottom_right"><strong><u>A) Managing Director : </strong></u>  </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td align="left" valign="top" class="Year1 border_left">
                                    <div align="justify">
                                        Bus Transport is the primary function of the PMPML. Responsibility of  controlling the bus transport has been assigned to the Managing Director.  Reviewing the existing routes, altering them if necessary, attending to the  demands and suggestions of the passengers, surveying and planning new routes,  management of the main bus stations and depots, assigning tasks to the staff  working at the depots, bus-station and buses and deciding their work-schedules  are the responsibilities of the Managing Director.<br>
                                        The head of  all the depots and main bus stations, transport planning and execution  officers, transport supervisory staff are accountable to the Managing Director.  To preserve lost property of the passengers, ensure their return after  ascertaining the identity of the claimant, to attend to PMPML accidents, take  measures for preventing accidents, conduct departmental enquiries of staff are  the tasks which fall under the preview of the Managing Director officer.
                                    </div>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td align="left" valign="top" class="Year1 border_top_left"><u><strong>B) Joint Managing Director :</strong></u></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td height="60" align="left" valign="top" class="Year1 border_left">He is responsible for over  all functioning of the company. The following officers except <strong><u>Chief Executive Officer</u></strong>&nbsp; are placed under him.<br>
                                    <br>
                                    <strong>1</strong><strong>)</strong><strong> Chief  Engineer : </strong>

                                    <p>
                                        Efficient use of the bus-vehicles, repairs and  maintenance, implementing the regulations in the Pollution laws and Motor  Transport Act are the chief responsibilities of the Chief Engineer. Overall  maintenance and upkeep of the buses is his primary responsibility. He controls  the Central Workshop as well as the repairs and maintenance sections of all the  depots and main bus stations. To see that there is an adequate supply of tools  and implements necessary for repairs and maintenance, spare parts, tyres, fuel  and related incidental items and monitor their optimum usage, keep a record of  fuel efficiency of the buses, their comparative studies, take measures for  maximum fuel efficiency of the vehicles, make an "age-wise analysis"  of the vehicles, get the vehicles passed through the RTO department are the  tasks that fall under the preview of the Chief Engineer.<br>
                                        Staff in the Central Workshop,  Maintenance Heads and other staff in all the depots and main bus stations,  technicians and technical staff, Stores manager are all accountable to the  Chief Engineer.<p></p>
                                    </p>

                                    <strong>2</strong><strong>)</strong><strong> Traffic  Manager : </strong>
                                    <p>
                                        Route planning, Route Scheduling,  Time table, Sports event, Cultural&nbsp;  planning, Advertisement on bus, bus shelter are been managed by him.
                                    </p>

                                    <strong>3</strong><strong>)</strong><strong> Civil Engineer  : </strong>
                                    <p>
                                        The responsibility of maintenance and repairs  of all PMPML buildings, commercial complexes, main bus stations, main depots,  staff colonies, bus-stops lies with the Civil Engineer. The Head Office   Building and Central  Workshop at Swargate, Commercial Complexes at Swargate, Hadapsar and Deccan  Gymkhana, six main depots and 18 main bus stations are all looked after and  maintained by the Civil Engineer's office.<br>
                                    </p>

                                    <strong>4</strong><strong>)</strong><strong> Chief  Accounts and Finance Officer : </strong>
                                    <p>He is responsible for the transaction related  to financial matters of the company.</p>
                                    <strong>5</strong><strong>)</strong><strong> Administrative Officer : </strong>
                                    <p>
                                        The Administrative Officer has primarily  administrative responsibilities. Matters such as appointments, salaries,  promotions, retirements of staff are taken care of by him.<br>
                                    </p>
                                    <strong>6</strong><strong>)</strong><strong> Security Officer : .</strong>
                                    <p>Matters related to the safety and security of the company  is their looked by him.</p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td align="left" valign="top" class="Year1 border_top_left"><strong><u>C) Chief Executive Officer : </u></strong></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td align="left" valign="top" class="Year1 border_left">All the function of Company Secretary,  calculating conducting meetings of Board of Directors, preparing resolutions as  per discussion, preparing as per document notes, <strong>&nbsp;</strong>implementation of the  discussion by Board of Directors.
												<br>
                                    The main function of PMPML,  are thus divided and carried out. The total staff of PMPML is nearly eight and  half thousand. Out of these, around the hundred work in the offices. The  remaining six and half thousand are drivers-conductors-workers. It is their  collective effort that keeps the PMPML running.</td>
